<h2>Wordbook</h2>
<h4>Statement:</h4>
<p><b>Develop an explanation dictionary. Give all the words where they occur and decrypt them by a given combination of letters.</b> <i>(Variant: 6 of 14, order in group: 20)</i></p>
<p>Create web- applications using Struts. Logging in into application occurs by entering a name and password. Implement two groups of users: admins (can do all including user management) and users (limited in scope, they only have access to their own account). Process validation errors using Struts. Provide internationalization. Suggest a decent user interface (menus, etc.).</p>
<h4>Developed solution description:</h4>
<p>Features:</p>
<ul>
	<li>comfortable working with the dictionary : search, alphabetical sorting , pagination;</li>
	<li>wordbook editing: adding, altering and deleting words;</li>
	<li>registration and authentication;</li>
	<li>user authentication and access rights;</li>
	<li>user management: role assignment, password changing, deletion;</li>
	<li> internationalization: Belarus, English and Russian languages.</li>
</ul>
<p>Following technologies and software products were used:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Java&trade; &mdash; the programming language;</li>
	<li>Apache Struts 2&trade; &mdash; framework for creating Java EE web applications;</li>
	<li>Apache Maven&trade; &mdash; for the ease of building and deployment;</li>
	<li>MySQL Server&trade; &mdash; is used as a database;</li>
	<li>Twitter Bootstrap&trade; &mdash; to create a decent user interface;</li>
	<li>And also Struts 2 Bootstrap Plugin, Struts 2 Json Plugin, XStream and Apache Commons DBCP libraries.</li>
</ul>
<p>Eclipse IDE, Jetty Web Server and githib.com were also used in development process.. </p>
